The paper discusses a method for evaluating counterfactual queries in causal models, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of structural models, which are a type of mathematical model commonly used in economics and social sciences, suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computational economics (cs.CE). The mention of policies and control of variables suggests that the paper may also be relevant to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of mathematical models and analysis suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT).
